 asthmaHarmonizer
A smart R package to harmonize asthma study variables — now with AI help!

Overview
asthmaHarmonizer is a lightweight R package designed to standardize asthma-related variables across datasets.
It includes a built-in harmonized database and can dynamically use ChatGPT to enrich missing mappings!

Features
 Lookup variables using an internal harmonized database.

 Auto-assist with ChatGPT if a variable is not found.

 Auto-parse ChatGPT replies to extract full harmonization fields.

️ Auto-save new variables into backups (log/ folder) and into the dynamic database.

️ Timestamp tracking for every new variable.

 Supports major vocabularies like LOINC, SNOMED-CT, OMOP, RxNorm, ATC, EuroQol.

Installation
r
Copy
Edit
# First load all files while developing locally
devtools::load_all()
ake sure you have devtools, httr, jsonlite, dplyr, readr, cli installed.

 Example Usage
r
Copy
Edit
# Lookup an existing variable
lookup_variable("age")

# Lookup a missing variable — AI will help!
lookup_variable("fvc_measured")  # if not found, you can search via ChatGPT

# View all variables added dynamically
view_added_variables()
Dynamic Workflow
If a variable is not found:

You'll be asked if you want to use ChatGPT.

The output is parsed into fields:

Harmonized Name

UK Variable

Source Label / Description

Target Concept

Standard Vocabulary

Standard Concept Code

Match Confidence

Summary

You can choose to add it to your working database automatically!

Everything is saved and logged.

Setting Up ChatGPT Access
You need to set your API key:

r
Copy
Edit
Sys.setenv(OPENAI_API_KEY = "your-actual-api-key-here")
You can get your API key from platform.openai.com.

 Auto-backups and Logs
Every time a new variable is added:

A backup of the database is saved (harmonized_database_dynamic_backup.rds).

A CSV log file is saved into the log/ folder.

